We recommended and the Local Chief Executive agreed to instruct the Municipal Treasurer to – 

stop the practice of using cash reserve for trust liabilities for payment of regular expenditures to avoid the incurrence of cash deficit; 

promptly remit trust funds due to other government agencies; 

control disbursements based on available funds/appropriation and not on available cash balances; and

ensure that trust fund account are used only for the specific expenditures for which it was created or received.

We recommended and the Local Chief Executive agreed to instruct the Municipal Accountant to – 

cause the immediate liquidation of the cash advances granted to LGU officials/employees;

ensure that the liquidation reports are submitted to the Office of the COA Auditor for review, with all of the necessary documents attached therein, such as the official receipts, certificate of seminar/trainings completed, etc.; 

exert effort in locating documents on cash advances to properly establish the responsible accountable officer; and 

file appropriate charges against persons liable if warranted, for continuous failure to settle their accountabilities upon demand.

