We recommended the following courses of actions:

The immediate submission of the Reports of Actual Inventory of PPE;

Reconcile the result of the actual physical inventory report with the accounting record and investigate discrepancies as required in Section 491 of GAAM Volume I;

Property Cards and PPE Ledger Cards should be updated and properly maintained by the GSO and Accountant/Bookkeeper, respectively, in order to monitor the acquired assets of the municipality in compliance with Section 43 of the NGAS Manual ; and

Depreciation of the acquired properties and equipment should be properly computed and recorded in the books of the municipality to correctly reflect the value of the assets.

